'''March 22''' is the 22nd day of the month {{ill|March (Lunisolar)|ja|3月 (旧暦)|lt=March (Yayoi)|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/March (Lunisolar)|qq=}}, the 3rd month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}} day is {{ill|Shakkō|ja|赤口|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shakkō|1=Shakkō|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q11635368}}.

== Events ==
* {{ill|Taika (era)|en|Taika (era)|qid=Q1077930|lt=Taika|1=Taika (era)}} 2nd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|646|en|646|qid=Q33285|lt=646|1=646}} {{ill|April 12|en|April 12|qid=Q2499|lt=April 12|1=April 12}}) – The {{ill|Sōsōryō|ja|薄葬令|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sōsōryō|1=Thin Burial Edict|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q11622174}} is issued, prohibiting the construction of large tombs and the practice of having retainers commit ritual suicide upon their lord’s death.
* {{ill|Kōryaku|en|Kōryaku|qid=Q252777|lt=Kōryaku|1=Kōryaku}} 1st year / {{ill|Tenju|en|Tenju|qid=Q1145023|lt=Tenjū (Japan)|1=Tenju}} 5th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1379|en|1379|qid=Q6316|lt=1379|1=1379}} {{ill|April 9|en|April 9|qid=Q2504|lt=April 9|1=April 9}}) – The Northern Court changes the era name from {{ill|Eiwa|en|Eiwa|qid=Q1145780|lt=Eiwa (Japan)|1=Eiwa}} to {{ill|Kōryaku|en|Kōryaku|qid=Q252777|lt=Kōryaku|1=Kōryaku}}.
* {{ill|Meiji era|en|Meiji era|qid=Q3125096|lt=Meiji era|1=Meiji era}} 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1870|en|1870|qid=Q7741|lt=1870|1=1870}} {{ill|April 22|en|April 22|qid=Q2526|lt=April 22|1=April 22}}) – The {{ill|Tokyo Prefecture (1868–1943)|en|Tokyo Prefecture (1868–1943)|qid=Q1189121|lt=Tokyo Prefecture (1868–1943)|1=Tokyo Prefecture (1868–1943)}} grants permission for the operation of {{ill|Pulled rickshaw|en|Pulled rickshaw|qid=Q16337999|lt=rickshaws|1=Pulled rickshaw}}.

